Program: Discovery
Title: Anti-Sense - shooting the messenger
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwsw
Last Broadcast Date: 20 January 1997
A look at anti-sense medicine, which cancels out the effect of harmful genes. By taking a mirror image of the gene you want to target scientists are hoping that they can form a duplex that will stop the gene being replicated as a protein, an effect which could help prevent diseases including cancer. Also in the programme, getting close to plants in a search for answers and a look at what may happen at the end of time. Show less